<% content_for :meta_title, "GitLocker FAQ" %>
<% content_for :meta_description,  "Check our Frequently Asked Questions" %>
<div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-700 to-orange-500">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-24 sm:pt-32 lg:px-8 lg:py-40">
    <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 lg:gap-8">
      <div class="lg:col-span-5">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-mono leading-10 tracking-tight text-gray-900">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">Can’t find the answer you’re looking for? Reach out to our support team at cody@gitlocker.com.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 lg:col-span-7 lg:mt-0">
        <dl class="space-y-10">
          <div>
            <dt class="text-base font-semibold leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">How do I get started buying and selling code on the marketplace?</dt>
            <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">In order to buy and sell code on the marketplace all you need to do is make an account with GitLocker using your GitHub account. From there, in order to buy a product just browse through the marketplace to find a product you want and then when you find a product you like, click add to cart and then checkout. In order to sell, you need to click "add product" in the dropdown menu when you click on your user icon in the navigation bar. Follow the instructions on the "add product" page.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="text-base font-semibold leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">What kind of repositories can I sell?</dt>
            <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">You can sell any private GitHub repository that is currently in your GitHub account or any local repository on your computer.</dd>
          </div>
           <div>
            <dt class="text-base font-semibold font-mono leading-7 text-gray-900">How much do I get to keep on my sales in the marketplace?</dt>
            <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">You get to keep 90% of your sales.</dd>
          </div>
           <div>
            <dt class="text-base font-semibold leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">How many products can I list on the marketplace?</dt>
            <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">Unlimited</dd>
          </div>
           <div>
            <dt class="text-base font-semibold font-mono leading-7 text-gray-900">How do I get paid in the marketplace?</dt>
            <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">Go to the "Get Paid" section in the dropdown menu when you click on your user icon in the navigation bar and click the button to withdraw via Stripe. There is a 7 day holding period giving the buyer a chance to ask for a refund.</dd>
          </div>
           <div>
            <dt class="text-base font-semibold font-mono leading-7 text-gray-900">How do I create a private repository on GitHub?</dt>
            <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">Use this link to learn how to configure a private GitHub repository: <span class="font-bold underline"><%=link_to "Making a GitHub Repo", "https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/creating-and-managing-repositories/quickstart-for-repositories", :target => "_blank" %></span></dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="text-base font-semibold font-mono leading-7 text-gray-900">Where do I go to write code?</dt>
            <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">You can go to <span class="font-bold underline"><%=link_to "replit.com", "https://replit.com", :target => "_blank" %></span> and create a project using one of their templates or start from scratch. Additionally, you can use GitLocker's web IDE by clicking "Write Code" on our home page.</dd>
          </div>
           <div>
            <dt class="text-base font-semibold font-mono leading-7 text-gray-900">Where do I go to learn more about coding?</dt>
            <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 font-mono text-gray-900">You can go to <span class="font-bold underline"><%=link_to "coding resources", resources_path %></span> to see all the different free and paid options for learning to code.</dd>
          </div>

          <!-- More questions... -->
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
